Mozambique, Korea Bank Agree on Solar Loan, Radio Mozambique Says

-- B y   F r e d   K a t e r e r e
-- 
2011-10-14T05:04:22Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-14/mozambique-korean-bank-sign-loan-accord-radio-mozambique-says.html
Export-Import Bank of  Korea  signed a
$60 million loan agreement with Mozambique to fund a solar-panel
project and an emergency-information management system, Radio
Mozambique reported.  The loan, which carries an interest rate of 0.01 percent,
will be repaid over a 40-year period, including a 15-year grace
period, the Maputo-based broadcaster said, citing Mozambican
Finance Minister Manuel Chang. The loan accord was signed
yesterday by Chang and Sang Wan Byun, vice president of the
South Korean lender, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Fred Katerere in Maputo at 
 fkaterere@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Paul Richardson  at 
 pmrichardson@bloomberg.net  